cashire, England, United Kingdom","Farneworth, Lancs., England":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Molyneux","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): occupational name from Old French <i>molineux</i> ‘miller’, a variant of <i>molineur</i>, <i>molinier</i>. See   Mulliner  .","English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from an unidentified French placename.","Irish: adoption for   Mulligan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mullineaux","meanings":["Irish and English (Lancashire): variant of   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Mulliner","meanings":["English: occupational name for a miller, from Old French <i>molinier</i> ‘miller’. Compare   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Molineaux","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Staffordshire): variant of   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Molyneaux","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): variant of   Molyneux  . Compare   Mallonee  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Molyneux was born about 1397, in Radcliffe, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She married James de Hulton in 1414. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died on 15 August 1442, in Farnworth, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"ABT 1397–15 August 1442":"umbes 1397–15. august 1442","1388–Male":"1388–Surnud","1419–Male":"1419–Surnud","1421–Male":"1421–Surnud","1424–1460":"1424–1460","1427–Female":"1427–Surnud","1397–1442":"1397–1442","ABT 1419":"umbes 1419","abt.1427":"umbes 1427","1460":"1460","abt 1421":"umbes 1421","1414":"1414","1424":"1424","ABT 1397":"umbes 1397","1421":"1421","1388":"1388","1442":"1442","15 August 1442":"15. august 1442","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","1427":"1427","Farnsworth, Lancs., Eng.":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Farnworth, Lancashire, England":"Farnworth, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Radcliffe, Lancaster, England, Great Britain":"Radcliffe, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Farnworth, Lancaster, England":"Farnworth, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Farneworth, Lancs., England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1397–15 August 1442":"noin 1397–15. elokuuta 1442","1388–Male":"1388–Kuollut","1419–Male":"1419–Kuollut","1421–Male":"1421–Kuollut","1424–1460":"1424–1460","1427–Female":"1427–Kuollut","1397–1442":"1397–1442","ABT 1419":"noin 1419","abt.1427":"noin 1427","1460":"1460","abt 1421":"noin 1421","1414":"1414","1424":"1424","ABT 1397":"noin 1397","1421":"1421","1388":"1388","1442":"1442","15 August 1442":"15. elokuuta 1442","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","1427":"1427","Farnsworth, Lancs., Eng.":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Farnworth, Lancashire, England":"Farnwort